Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams}(into 2cm chunks) - no need to peel.

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1}, then slice one half into half moons.

Trim the @green beans{150%grams}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}.

Finely chop the @chives{1%bunch} (use scissors if easier). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Lay the @British chicken breasts{2} on a baking tray, drizzle with oil, sprinkle over the @dried oregano{1%sachet} and season with salt and pepper. Top with the lemon slices.

Roast the chicken on the top shelf of your #oven{} until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Garlicky Green Beans ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in half the garlic, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

== Chive Butter Sauce ==

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

Add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the remaining garlic and cook, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @chicken stock paste{10%grams} and @water{75%milliliters} for the sauce. Bring to the boil and simmer until reduced slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @butter{20%grams} until melted, then remove from the heat. Stir in half the chives and a squeeze of lemon juice from the reserved lemon.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and more lemon juice if needed.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, add the lemon zest and remaining chives to the roasted potato chunks. Toss to combine.

Slice the chicken breasts into 2cm thick slices and share between your plates. Serve the potato chunks and garlicky green beans alongside.

Spoon the chive butter sauce over the chicken.

Enjoy!